Norton Community Terms and Conditions of Use

The Norton Community and its associated boards, blogs, discussion forums, personal message tool, content and services (the "Community Website") are provided by NortonLifeLock Inc. together with its affiliates (collectively, "NortonLifeLock", “we”, "us", and "our") to its customers (individual consumers above the age of eighteen (18) years) (referenced below as “you” or “your”) for their own and personal use of the Community Website.

These Norton Community Terms and Conditions of Use (“Community Terms”) govern your rights and obligations upon which you may use the Community Website. Other websites operated by NortonLifeLock may have their own terms and conditions.

By clicking "Accept Terms & Conditions of Use" or otherwise electronically indicating assent, you agree to the terms and conditions of the Community Terms.

If you have accepted multiple versions of the Community Terms, the most current version that you accepted is the Community Terms between you and us and supersedes and replaces all prior versions.

1. DESCRIPTION OF THE COMMUNITY WEBSITED

The Community Website is designed to create and support an online community where, subject to all of their obligations under the Community Terms, and other pertinent NortonLifeLock-related agreements, our customers can: (a) can share their experiences about  our products and services; and (b) more easily receive information from us about our products and services. Certain services or areas of the Community Website may not be available to all our customers. You agree not to use any services, or access any areas of the Community Website, that we have not specifically authorized you to use or access.

2. REGISTRATION

In some cases, we may permit certain participants who are already registered with NortonLifeLock to access the Community Website without re-registration. In those cases, the participants will be deemed a "Registered Participant" upon their acceptance of these Community Terms. In other cases, to access the Community Website, you may be required to register for an account by completing our participant registration form. After our review of your registration information, we may issue a Participant User ID and password to you, in which case you shall become a "Registered Participant" after acceptance of these Community Terms. In addition, you may be invited to provide personal profile information that may be used by us in accordance with our Global Privacy Statement and viewed by other participants. Further information about registration, personal profiles, and our use of your information can be found here.

You represent and warrant that all the information that you provide to us in the participant registration form is truthful and accurate. If you provide any false, inaccurate, or incomplete information in your participant registration form, we may immediately terminate your account and access.

Registered Participants are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of their passwords and  shall not share their Participant User IDs or passwords with anyone. You agree to immediately notify us of any unauthorized use of any Participant User ID or password. You will be solely responsible and liable for any and all access to, and use of, the Community Website (including all activities and transactions) by any person logging in under your account.

3. USE OF DOCUMENTS

Except as otherwise indicated on the Community Website, you may download, view, copy and print documents, including graphics incorporated in the documents, that we publish on the Community Website ("Documents"), including but not limited to, white papers, press releases, datasheets and FAQs subject to the following:

     (a) the Documents may be used solely for personal, informational, non-commercial purposes;

     (b) the Documents may not be copied or posted on any network computer or broadcasted in any media;

