     (d) the Documents may not be modified or altered in any way.

Except as set forth above in this Section and where your use constitutes an exception to copyright law (also known in some countries as “fair use”), you may not use, download, upload, copy, print, display, perform, reproduce, publish, license, post, transmit or distribute any Documents or other content from the Community Website in whole or in part without the express authorization of NortonLifeLock.

Use for any other purpose is expressly prohibited by law and may result in severe civil and criminal penalties.

Documents do not include the layout or design of the Community Website. Elements of the Community Website are protected by trade dress or other laws and may not be imitated or reproduced in whole or in part. Documents do not include logos, graphics, sounds or images on this Community Website, which may be reproduced or distributed only when expressly set forth herein.

Materials uploaded to the Communication Website may be subject to posted limitations on usage, reproduction and/or dissemination; you are responsible for adhering to such limitations if you download the materials.

Any uses of the information from the Community Website that differ from those described above must be authorized in writing by NortonLifeLock.

Any posted Documents may be updated, deleted, or modified by NortonLifeLock from time to time without prior notice.

4. DISCUSSION FORUMS AND FORUM CONTENT

    4.1. Discussions Forums

We may offer you access to one or more discussion forums, chat areas, bulletin boards, news group, blog, wiki, email, or other service ("Discussion Forums") in which you can upload, email, post, publish or otherwise access or transmit Forum Content, as defined below, and where you may access our product and service information, development tools, utilities, pre-release, experimental or commercially available NortonLifeLock products and services, as well as post questions and discuss issues related to our products and services with other participant, and, in certain appropriate forums, post scripts or sample code for discussion purposes (collectively, "Forum Content").

    4.2. Forum Content

You acknowledge that all Forum Content may be viewed and copied by other Community Website’s participants, and that you are responsible for complying with all of your legal obligations about protecting the proprietary and confidential nature of our products and services in choosing what to post or upload.

    4.3. No Liability

You agree that NortonLifeLock is not responsible for and will have no liability in connection with any Forum Content posted or uploaded to the Discussion Forum by you or other participants. We do not specifically monitor, ensure or confirm accuracy of, or provide input or support for these Discussion Forums. Rather, we sponsor the Discussion Forum as a platform or venue for our customers to participate in the exchange of ideas and product and service expertise. All such information is provided on a voluntary basis. Without limiting the foregoing, NortonLifeLock has and shall have no liability regarding the accuracy of such Forum Content, and you use such Forum Content entirely at your own risk.

5. ACCEPTABLE USE AND CONDUCT

    5.1. No monitoring

We do not control or endorse the content, messages or information found in any Forum Content and, therefore, we specifically disclaim any liability with regard to the Community Website and any actions resulting from your participation in any of the foregoing. The view of hosts or participants who are not authorized NortonLifeLock spokespersons do not necessarily reflect those of NortonLifeLock. You are solely responsible for your interactions with others through the Community Website.

Participants are asked to refrain from posting advertisements or solicitations not pertaining to the intended use and purpose of the Discussion Forums. Specifically, and without limitation:

- you shall not upload, email, post, publish, distribute or otherwise transmit any Forum Content containing a solicitation of funds, promotion, advertising, solicitation for products or services, or other commercial matter;

- you agree not to solicit other participants of the Community Website to use or join or become members of any commercial online or offline service or other organization;

- you agree not to collect or store personal data about other participants.

NortonLifeLock cannot and does not make any guarantee with respect to the accuracy, inoffensiveness, or suitability of any content that appears on the Community Website.

    5.2. Prohibited Conduct

You agree not to use the Community Website for any purpose that is unlawful or prohibited by these Community Terms or the rules, guidelines or terms and conditions posted for a specific area of the Community Website.

We reserve the right to improve the Community Website and to better enhance your experience with, and use of, the Community Website by prohibiting certain conduct and removing Forum Content (including without limitation, illegal, outdated or inaccurate information, profanity, personal attacks, slurs and the like, and/or banning participants from participating in any or all of the Discussion Forums), and by administering and moderating the Community Website. Consequently, you agree not to:

    upload, post, email, transmit, or otherwise make available any Forum Content that is unlawful, harmful (including harmful to NortonLifeLock's reputation), threatening, abusive, harassing, tortious, defamatory, vulgar, obscene, libelous, invasive of another's privacy, hateful, or racially, ethnically, or otherwise objectionable;
    use the Community Website in connection with surveys, contests, pyramid schemes, chain letters, junk email, spamming or any duplicative or unsolicited messages (commercial or otherwise);
    impersonate any person or entity;
    violate the legal rights of another party, such as by infringing another's intellectual property rights through the posting, uploading or use of Forum Content (including without limitation, photographs or images), including but not limited to, infringing copyright or trademark laws, or rights of privacy or publicity, or any other proprietary rights, unless you own or control the rights thereto or have received all necessary consent to do the same;
    forge email headers or otherwise manipulate identifiers in order to disguise the origin of any information transmitted through the Community Website;
    use the Community Website or the Discussion Forums to compile commercial, political, or charitable mailing lists or to facilitate the transmission of spam, junk email, chain letters, or obscene or profane content;
    upload, post, email, transmit, or otherwise make available any unsolicited or unauthorized advertising or promotional materials (including sweepstakes materials);
    post direct links to executable files (.exe) that are not from a NortonLifeLock domain;
    harvest or otherwise collect information about others, including e-mail addresses;
    use, download, copy, or provide (whether or not for a fee) to a person or entity any directory of the Community Website’s participants or other people, or usage information or any portion thereof;
    upload files that contain viruses, Trojan horses, worms, time bombs, cancelbots, corrupted files, or any other similar software or programs that may damage the operation of another's computer or property of another;
    falsify or delete any copyright management information, such as author attributions, legal or other proper notices or proprietary designations or labels of the origin or source of software or other material contained in a file that is uploaded;
    restrict or inhibit any other participant from using and enjoying the Community Website or Discussion Forums;
    create multiple accounts on the Community Website, or create a false identity for the purpose of misleading others;
    solicit kudos or solutions from other participants to their own posts;
    violate any applicable laws or regulations;
    engage in tortious talk, harass, threaten any other individual, or engage in other disruptive conduct in a Discussion Forum;
    access or use the Community Website in any manner that could damage, disable, overburden, or impair any NortonLifeLock accounts, computer systems or networks;
    attempt to gain unauthorized access to any parts of the Community Website or any NortonLifeLock accounts, computer systems or networks;
    interfere or attempt to interfere with the proper working of the Community Website or any NortonLifeLock accounts, computer systems or networks;
    use any robot, spider, scraper or other automated means to access the Community Website or any NortonLifeLock accounts, computer systems or networks.  

